		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">MSNBC - Gamers willing to subscribe to play</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=381827" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    MSNBC online has a new article regarding some of the current state of the MMORPG player base. Check it out:
<blockquote>
<p>
Feb. 28 — Pissed-off gnomes from the land of Norrath have launched a lawsuit against Sony Online Entertainment because Sony won’t let them buy and sell magic armor on eBay for use in an online game called EverQuest. Over in Dereth, the online fantasy world where the game Asheron’s Call takes place, “a severe bug impacting the economy” has led furious message-board warriors to curse corporate overlords Microsoft and Turbine Entertainment.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>
Head over and check it out: <a href="http://www.msnbc.com/news/537377.asp">http://www.msnbc.com/news/537377.asp</a></p>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
