				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Actually, the article did mean selling their audiences. It's kind <BR>
of like product placement in a movie, or pop up ads. The actual value<BR>
in any one who plays the game, is in direct or indirect advertising.<BR>
This could be done by selling addresses for direct mail, or more<BR>
indirect (or maybe more direct) placement of products in the game.<BR>
/You have been poisoned w/ Exlax...<BR>
/You have been slashed by a 3d Dorito...<BR>
Okay, not real funny or practical, but you get the idea. If a company <BR>
can cut costs or bring more revenue in by doing these things, they<BR>
will. Because we don't look or respond to commercials or banners,<BR>
the ad companies have to get to you somehow. Why not where you<BR>
spend your time. The movies, TV, and Everquest?
